				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A question about mezzing<a name="22872"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 21 04 11:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This is a real pain for anyone who is mezzing, be it Bard, Enc or Necro.
<br />

<br />
Only way to target properly, is to mezz one, then tell the tank to back up a few steps, then mez another.
<br />

<br />
This is commonly known as seperating the mobs or &quot;sepping&quot;.
<br />

<br />
I usually tell the tank &quot;Sep pls&quot; and unless its a random tank off the LFG list or a stranger, they'll usually know what to do. If they dont, just explain it to them.
<br />

<br />
And no, there is NO way to tab/toggle through all the mobs, only thing to do is click / hit F8. Optionally you can use the lower level mez that will move the mob one step each time it lands to seperate them yourself.
<br />

<br />
I only use Lullaby of Morell, and this one will leave the mob at his exact spot when being mezzed (which is a great relief IMO since I wont have to bother about pushing/pulling mobs off a ledge, into the walls et.c)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Enadil Elvensinger
