			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A question about mezzing<a name="22884"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 21 04 2:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A couple things you can do:
<br />

<br />
1)  if you are using the lvl 28, 40, or 53 mez, they all move the mob a little (28 and 40 push, 53 pulls toward you).  This helps a bit in spreading them out.
<br />

<br />
2)  It's kind of a pain to keep a song slot for this, but since you weren't pulling, your Lull spot should be open, hehe...  Have the lvl 20 AE Slow memmed.  It does no damage, but will get their attention.  Zap it once, and by the next tick, the mobs will be on you.
<br />

<br />
Esc.  First mob hits you, Mez... back up. mez lands
<br />
Esc. to lose target again, second add hits you, Mez... keep backing up
<br />
Esc. Third add hits, Mez...
<br />

<br />
Now move to the side and notice the nice line of mobs you have.  Now you can mouse target each and keep them mezzed in a cycle.
<br />

<br />
There is the Toggle Targets buffer, and if you don't have that mapped yet, you most certainly should.  I twist with my left hand on the number keys, so I mapped mine to &quot;Q&quot;.  If you only have two adds, or once you are down to two adds, you can simply Mez, Toggle, Mez, Toggle... and keep those two locked down all day.  I have done this once when our healer was OOM and kept the mobs locked down while he medded before too.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=564823">Scherzo Glissando </a><BR>
Maestro, Molto Espressivo</span></td>
